<node id="class:se.citerus.dddsample.domain.model.cargo.Cargo">
  <data key="d0">"class:se.citerus.dddsample.domain.model.cargo.Cargo"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cargo"</data>
  <data key="d2">"clase"</data>
  <data key="d3">""</data>
  <data key="d4">{"fan_in": 0, "fan_out": 0}</data>
  <data key="d5">{}</data>
  <data key="d6">[]</data>
  <data key="d7">false</data>
  <data key="d8">null</data>
  <data key="d9">"Java class cargo located in package se.citerus.dddsample.domain.model.cargo. Implements interfaces cargo, domain entity. Uses related classes cargo, delivery, handling history, itinerary, leg, route specification, tracking id. Defines methods assign to route, cargo, delivery, derive delivery progress, equals, hash code, id, itinerary, origin, route specification, same identity as, specify new route, to string, tracking id."</data>
  <data key="d10">"The Cargo class is responsible for managing cargo information, including its identity, origin, route specification, and itinerary, and provides operations to assign routes, track delivery progress, and specify new routes. It also allows for equality checks and string representation."</data>
