<node id="class:se.citerus.dddsample.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt">
  <data key="d0">"class:se.citerus.dddsample.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt"</data>
  <data key="d1">"HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt"</data>
  <data key="d2">"clase"</data>
  <data key="d3">""</data>
  <data key="d4">{"fan_in": 0, "fan_out": 0}</data>
  <data key="d5">{}</data>
  <data key="d6">[]</data>
  <data key="d7">false</data>
  <data key="d8">null</data>
  <data key="d9">"Java class handling event registration attempt located in package se.citerus.dddsample.interfaces.handling. Uses related classes handling event, tracking id, un locode, voyage number. Defines methods get completion time, get registration time, get tracking id, get type, get un locode, get voyage number, handling event registration attempt, to string."</data>
  <data key="d10">"The HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt class is responsible for managing event registration attempts, providing access to attributes such as completion time, registration time, tracking ID, type, UN/LOCODE, and voyage number. It appears to be a data container or a value object, encapsulating information related to an event registration attempt."</data>
