  <data key="d9">"Java class infrastructure messaging jms config located in package se.citerus.dddsample.infrastructure.messaging.jms. Uses related classes application events, cargo handled consumer, cargo inspection service, handling event registration attempt consumer, handling event service, jms application events impl, simple logging consumer. Defines methods application events, cargo handled consumer, cargo handled queue, connection, create queue, delivered cargo consumer, delivered cargo queue, handling event registration attempt consumer, handling event registration attempt queue, jms connection factory, jms operations, listener container factory, misdirected cargo consumer, misdirected cargo queue, rejected registration attempts consumer, rejected registration attempts queue, session."</data>
  <data key="d10">"The InfrastructureMessagingJmsConfig class is responsible for managing JMS (Java Message Service) configuration and providing access to JMS-related operations. It appears to be a configuration class that sets up JMS queues, connections, and listeners for various messaging scenarios."</data>
