  <data key="d9">"Java class interfaces application context located in package se.citerus.dddsample.interfaces. Uses related classes application events, booking service, booking service facade, booking service facade impl, cargo repository, cargo tracking rest service, handling event repository, location repository, track command validator, upload directory scanner, voyage repository. Defines methods add interceptors, booking service facade, cargo tracking rest service, locale resolver, message source, my scheduler, track command validator, upload directory scanner."</data>
  <data key="d10">"The InterfacesApplicationContext class is responsible for managing the application context, providing access to various services and components such as booking, cargo tracking, and message resolution. It offers methods to add interceptors, retrieve specific services, and interact with related components like validators and scanners."</data>
