<node id="class:com.pathfinder.api.TransitPath">
  <data key="d0">"class:com.pathfinder.api.TransitPath"</data>
  <data key="d1">"TransitPath"</data>
  <data key="d2">"clase"</data>
  <data key="d3">"Clase TransitPath"</data>
  <data key="d4">{"fan_in": 0, "fan_out": 0}</data>
  <data key="d5">{"archivo": "monoliths/cargo/TransitPath.java"}</data>
  <data key="d6">[]</data>
  <data key="d7">false</data>
  <data key="d8">null</data>
  <data key="d9">"Java class transit path located in package com.pathfinder.api. Uses related classes transit edge. Defines methods get transit edges, transit path."</data>
  <data key="d10">"The TransitPath class, located in the com.pathfinder.api package, is responsible for managing transit paths and providing access to their constituent edges. It offers a constructor method and a getTransitEdges method to retrieve the edges associated with the path."</data>
