  <data key="d9">"Java class external routing service located in package se.citerus.dddsample.infrastructure.routing. Implements interfaces routing service. Uses related classes graph traversal service, itinerary, leg, location repository, route specification, transit edge, transit path, un locode, voyage number, voyage repository. Defines methods external routing service, fetch routes for specification, is satisfying route spec, to itinerary, to leg."</data>
  <data key="d10">"The ExternalRoutingService class is responsible for managing external routing operations, providing methods to fetch routes for a given specification and convert them into itineraries and legs. It appears to interact with external routing data and possibly other infrastructure services to perform these operations."</data>
